cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper discusses the use of sparsity-inspired CSI acquisition techniques for massive MIMO, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves mathematical theory (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the design of acquisition algorithms. Additionally, the paper focuses on the overall system perspective (cs.MM) and the trade-offs between different duplexing modes.
